Tiny utility to enable MTK swap mechanism.


WHAT IT DOES?
=============
tiny_mkswap is used to set up a swap area.
tiny_swapon/tiny_swapoff is used to enable/disable a swap area for swapping.
tiny_switch is a used to determine whether we should enable swap.
tiny_fallocate is used to preallocate space for a swap file.


HOW IT WAS BUILT?
==================
It needs the following library from AOSP:
1.  libc.so
2.  libcutils.so


HOW TO USE IT?
==============
Provide executableS for MTK swap mechanism.
